  "market_context": "NQ 60-minute chart showing a series of failure swing highs above and a swing low coinciding with the previous day's low. Price approaches the prior day low area, setting up a potential sweep before a reversal higher toward unmitigated buy-side liquidity.",
  "key_observation": "Sweeping the previous day's low creates high resistance liquidity on the lower time frame, and with failure swings stacked above as draw on liquidity, the swept low should hold and price should trade up to those highs.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify the series of failure swing highs above as the draw on liquidity that price is targeting.",
    "Step 2: Recognize that for those highs to be reached, a sweep of a low (high resistance liquidity) is needed first.",
    "Step 3: Note that price swept the low which coincides with the previous day's low, creating high resistance liquidity at an important level.",
    "Step 4: Anticipate the swept low to hold and price to trade up to the failure swing highs above."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price held the swept previous day low and traded higher toward the failure swing highs as anticipated.",
  "lessons": "By combining the concepts of low resistance liquidity (failure swings) as targets and high resistance liquidity (sweeps of important levels like previous day low) as the origin, a directional idea can be framed cleanly on the lower time frame.",
